<TR> <TD ALIGN=CENTER>
<B> THE DYING GAUL &nbsp; <FONT CLASS="green">(MUSEI CAPITOLINI, ROME)</FONT> </B>
<TR> <TD>
This is a Roman copy of one of the statues from the victory monument erected by <A HREF="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Attalus_I">Attalus I</A> at <A HREF="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pergamon">Pergamum</A>  soon after 230 B.C., in commemoration of a series of victories which he had won over the Gauls who had invaded Asia Minor.  It depicts one of the chieftains of the Gauls, dying from a wound sustained in the fighting.  Before its connection with Attalus was recognised, the statue was believed to represent a dying gladiator.  
<TR> <TD> &nbsp;
